{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_19","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,160p' docs/changelog/changelog-2026-06-07.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Changelog 2026-06-07\n\n- Implemented a dependency-free MiniLang LSP server because the eval requires real protocol, parsing, diagnostics, and editor feature behavior from `src/server.mjs`.\n- Kept parsing tolerant and line-oriented so syntax errors publish diagnostics without blocking later symbols, completions, definitions, or hover results.\n- Reworked the MiniLang server pass to cover streamed JSON-RPC decoding, range-based incremental edits, forward function references, comments, scope-aware completions, and LSP feature responses with minimal dependency-free code.\n- Hardened shutdown handling so post-shutdown requests return a JSON-RPC error and notifications cannot mutate documents or diagnostics after the lifecycle boundary.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
